{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require affirmative consent for sexual activity",
        "additional_details": "We are living through a pandemic of sexual violence.\r\n \r\nPolice recorded 194,683 sexual offences, including 70,330 rape offences, in England and Wales in the year ending March 2022. This is the highest annual figure to date.\r\n \r\nWe need radical change to the law to get justice for women and men who are raped \u2013 and restore their confidence in the system.\r\n \r\nOther countries have introduced affirmative consent. In Sweden, new affirmative consent laws have seen conviction rates for rape go up by 75%.\r\n",
        "background": "Glamour UK and Right to Equality are calling on the Government to amend the Sexual Offences Act 2003 to implement a new definition of consent for sexual activity, in which defendants must show they took active steps to confirm they received informed, voluntary, active consent from the complainant.",
